            <p
                rend="This is a fragment of a news clipping.  There are notes (not in English) in both margins."/>
            <p><add>?</add> wives Jewesses, or at least let the children be circumcised and<lb/>
                stay with their fathers? Surely for no ˹other reason than this<lb/> that
                    <persName>Ezra</persName> did not want to disgrace the nation by making
                such<lb/> proselytes | and sport with the holy ˻Word of God, and make by-<lb/>ways
                and side-doors to the sacred edifice of our holy religion,<lb/> that every one may
                smuggle <del>himself</del> in and out whatever he<lb/> pleases, and thus suit every
                one's way of thinking, as <persName>Iben Ezra</persName><lb/> to
                    <persName>Ezra</persName> | vi. explains, <add>אולי הוציאום שלא היו גיורות
                    גמורות כרות המואביה</add>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Hoping that this may cause our people to change their<lb/> opinion
                concerning proselytes, I remain, dear sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Most respectfully yours,</p>
            <p><persName role="author">Dr. Illowy</persName>.</p>
            <p>Finfüger: <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>, <date>January 19, 1865</date></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <del>(The Occident, Vol. XXIII, No. 1 (<date>April 1865</date>), p. 30-33).</del>
            </p>
